                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.512/30: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rand</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-06-26T15:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1923—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reference Department’s 260 of May 8, 1923. Informed by British Chargé d’Affaires
                    that, since Spanish authorities have deposited with British consul all sums
                    which British claimed were illegally levied, King’s regulation dated June 2nd,
                    1923, has been issued ordering British subjects and protégés to pay tax.
                    Netherland nationals and protégés not paying tax.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rand</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
